# Trivy ignore list for findings we have evaluated and accepted.
#
# Format: one CVE id per line, with a comment explaining the reason
# the finding is accepted and a target date to re-evaluate.
#
# Re-evaluation policy: when bumping pmtiles or gdal-async, delete
# the relevant entries below first, then bump, then re-run Trivy. If
# the finding is gone, leave it deleted. If the finding remains under
# the new version, re-add the entry with the updated rationale.
#
# Review cadence: monthly, or any time the Security workflow goes red.

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# pmtiles Go binary (statically linked, embeds Go 1.26.1 stdlib).
# The vulnerabilities live in the embedded stdlib, not in code we
# control. The latest pmtiles release (v1.30.2, 2026-04-22) was cut
# before most of these CVEs were published, so upstream has not had
# the chance to rebuild against patched Go yet.
#
# Exposure analysis: the pmtiles binary in our image is invoked by
# TileLayerService.runPmtilesConvert (apps/portal-api/src/tile-layer/
# tile-conversion.ts) on uploaded MBTiles / zipped XYZ inputs. The
# inputs are uploaded by authenticated contributors and processed
# offline (worker queue, not on the request hot path). The Go net /
# net/mail / x/crypto bugs require attacker-controlled network input
# the binary never sees in our usage.
#
# Re-evaluate when pmtiles ships a release built with Go >= 1.27.
# Track upstream: https://github.com/protomaps/go-pmtiles/releases
CVE-2026-39883
CVE-2026-32280
CVE-2026-32281
CVE-2026-32283
CVE-2026-33810
CVE-2026-33811
CVE-2026-33814
CVE-2026-39820
CVE-2026-39836
CVE-2026-42499

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# gdal-async@3.12.3 ships @mapbox/node-pre-gyp as a bundledDependency
# (see "bundledDependencies" in its package.json). node-pre-gyp pulls
# tar@7.5.9 into the published tarball, which pnpm cannot override
# because the files are physically inside the package archive.
#
# Exposure analysis: node-pre-gyp's only job is to download the
# prebuilt native binary for gdal-async at INSTALL time. After
# install, nothing in the running portal-api process imports or
# invokes tar from that path. The CVEs require an attacker to feed
# malicious tarballs to the consuming code; nothing in our runtime
# does that.
#
# Re-evaluate when gdal-async ships a release bundling tar >= 7.5.11
# (or drops bundledDependencies). gdal-async latest is 3.12.3 as of
# 2026-05-18 so we wait on upstream.
CVE-2026-29786
CVE-2026-31802
